By Lubabalo Mashiqana South Africa’s land expropriation without compensation intentions have caught the attention of United States President Donald Trump. Trump tweeted on Thursday morning  This follows after SA’s President Cyril Ramaphosa had a Q&A on land expropriation in Parliament on Wednesday, and just over a month after land hearings began around the country. Apparently Trump’s tweet was motivated by the below Fox News insert. <iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/EThwj4NtnvU" width="560" height="315" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe> Trump’s comments sent the rand 1.87% lower to the dollar to 14.42 as fears spooked investors that sanctions could be imposed on South Africa.  